FBIS4-39672 "drsov111_c_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-111 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 Federal Assembly Yeltsin Approves Draft Laws Submitted to State Duma Yeltsin Approves Draft Laws Submitted to State Duma LD0806204794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1612 GMT 8 Jun 94 LD0806204794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Moscow June 8 TASS -- Persuant to the Treaty of Civic Accord Russian President Boris Yeltsin has approved a schedule for preparing draft laws to be submitted to the State Duma in June, 1994. The Russian president's representative in the Federal Assembly has been instructed to coordinate with the State Duma and the Russian Government to finalise draft laws to be considered by the lower house of parliament. Among them are draft laws establishing the procedure for passing and enacting federal laws, amending the law on the state border, bills on the juridicial system in the Russian Federation, on the Russian Government, on fighting organised crime and others.
